            "en-x-generated": "<p>Apply for your recognition from the Flemish government. </p><ul><li><a href=\"https://assets.vlaanderen.be/raw/upload/v1689852248/200204_Aanvraag_erkenning_MER-deskundige_k91gkb.docx\">Download the application form for recognition as an EIR expert</a> and complete it. You can apply for recognition in various <strong>disciplines and sub-domains.</strong> Also use the <strong>EIR completion list</strong> to make your application smoother. <ul><li><a href=\"https://assets.vlaanderen.be/raw/upload/v1652711647/170926_MER_invullijst_vwp3uj.xlsx\">EIA completion list</a>;</li><li><a href=\"https://assets.vlaanderen.be/image/upload/v1652711649/Handleiding_MER-invullijst_erbdon.pdf\">EIA completion list manual</a>.</li></ul></li><li>Transfer the one-off fee to account number BE40 3751 1110 2263 stating 'OMG-A-MER + your first and last name'.</li><li>Provide the necessary documents and proof of payment to the Flemish government.<ul><li>You have a Belgian eID: submit your application and proof of payment via the <a href=\"https://www.dev-vlaanderen.be/natuur-milieu-en-klimaat/erkenning-als-technicus-deskundige-opleidingscentrum-of-labo/erkenningenloket-omgeving\">online recognition counter of the Department of Environment</a> (log in with eID).</li><li>If you do not have a Belgian eID: send your application and proof of payment by registered letter to the Department of the Environment, Koning Albert II-laan 20/bus 8, 1000 Brussels, for the attention of Team Erkenningen, GOP division.</li></ul></li></ul><p>The competent department will process your application. A hearing may follow. The senior official of the Environment Department will take a decision within 90 days from the day after the submission of a complete application file.</p>",
